<subSubSection id="C34A6528FFEEFFCFA5CDFB571C8CFA64" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BEF36A3FFEEFFCFA5CDFB571D08FB68" blockId="30.[136,823,1166,1193]" box="[136,823,1166,1193]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<heading id="D0A781CFFFEEFFCFA5CDFB571D08FB68" box="[136,823,1166,1193]" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" reason="4">
10.3. 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFEEFFCFA582FB571CFAFB68" authority="Link (1821: 19)" authorityName="Link" authorityPageNumber="19" authorityYear="1821" box="[199,709,1166,1193]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Stachytarpheta" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hirsutissima">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFEEFFCFA582FB571C35FB69" bold="true" box="[199,522,1166,1193]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Stachytarpheta hirsutissima</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFEEFFCFA754FB571CFAFB68" author="Link, H. E." box="[529,709,1166,1192]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" refId="ref35140" refString="Link, H. E. (1821) Enumeratio Plantarum Horti regii botanici berolinensis altera 1. G. Reimer, Berlin, 458 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 66" type="book" year="1821">Link (1821: 19)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. (Fig. 3B)
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEF36A3FFEEFFCFA5CDFB0F1C8CFA64" blockId="30.[136,1452,1238,2093]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
Shrubs 
<quantity id="4CA89B46FFEEFFCFA59BFB0F1F6EFB31" box="[222,337,1238,1265]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.5" metricValueMax="15.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" unit="m" value="0.95" valueMax="1.5" valueMin="0.4">0.4‒1.5 m</quantity>
high, branches tetragonal, not winged, densely hirsute. Leaves opposite, sessile to short-petiolate, blade 2‒8 × 
<quantity id="4CA89B46FFEEFFCFA450FB231FA9FAD5" box="[277,406,1274,1301]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.35" metricValueMax="5.5" metricValueMin="1.2" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" unit="cm" value="3.35" valueMax="5.5" valueMin="1.2">1.2‒5.5 cm</quantity>
, chartaceous, ovate to rotund, apex obtuse or rounded, base truncate to obtuse, margin entire near the base, serrate toward the apex, ciliate, densely hirsute in both surfaces. Inflorescences 
<quantity id="4CA89B46FFEEFFCFA180FAC71B09FAF9" box="[1221,1334,1310,1337]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.05" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="1.1" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" unit="cm" value="30.5" valueMax="50.0" valueMin="11.0">11‒50 cm</quantity>
long, lax; bracts 
<quantity id="4CA89B46FFEEFFCFA597FA9B1F10FA9D" box="[210,303,1346,1373]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" unit="mm" value="7.0" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="6.0">6‒8 mm</quantity>
long, lanceolate, abaxial surface densely hirsute, margin ciliate; calyx 
<quantity id="4CA89B46FFEEFFCFA10DFA9B1A8FFA9D" box="[1096,1200,1346,1373]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="8.0" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" unit="cm" value="0.9" valueMax="1.0" valueMin="0.8">0.8‒1 cm</quantity>
long, immersed in the depressions of the rachis, 4-toothed, 1 sinus adaxial, densely hirsute externally; corolla 
<quantity id="4CA89B46FFEEFFCFA128FABF1AD4FA41" box="[1133,1259,1382,1409]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.15" metricValueMax="1.2" metricValueMin="1.1" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" unit="cm" value="1.15" valueMax="1.2" valueMin="1.1">1.1‒1.2 cm</quantity>
long, lilac. Fruit 
<quantity id="4CA89B46FFEEFFCFA5CDFA531EDAFA65" box="[136,229,1418,1445]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" unit="mm" value="4.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="4.0">4‒5 mm</quantity>
long, surrounded by the persistent calyx.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34A6528FFEEFFCEA5F8FA771C36FEE5" lastPageId="31" lastPageNumber="32" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BEF36A3FFEEFFCFA5F8FA771C51F9F5" blockId="30.[136,1452,1238,2093]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFEEFFCFA5F8FA771C2FFA08" bold="true" box="[189,528,1454,1480]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Distribution and habitat:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFEEFFCFA755FA771D70FA08" authorityName="Link" authorityYear="1821" box="[528,847,1454,1480]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Stachytarpheta" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hirsutissima">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFEEFFCFA755FA771D70FA08" box="[528,847,1454,1480]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Stachytarpheta hirsutissima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to 
<collectingCountry id="F3477633FFEEFFCFA143FA771A72FA08" box="[1030,1101,1454,1480]" name="Brazil" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, restricted to the 
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFEEFFCFA067FA761BB7FA08" box="[1314,1416,1455,1480]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">restingas</emphasis>
of 
<collectingRegion id="4994F841FFEEFFCFA5CDFA0B1ED8FA2C" box="[136,231,1490,1516]" country="Brazil" name="Alagoas" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Alagoas</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="4994F841FFEEFFCFA5B4FA0B1F0AFA2C" box="[241,309,1490,1516]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Bahia</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="4994F841FFEEFFCFA47AFA0B1FDEFA2C" box="[319,481,1490,1516]" country="Brazil" name="Espirito Santo" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Espírito Santo</collectingRegion>
, and 
<collectingRegion id="4994F841FFEEFFCFA75CFA0B1C87FA2C" box="[537,696,1490,1516]" country="Brazil" name="Rio de Janeiro" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Rio de Janeiro</collectingRegion>
states (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFEEFFCFA64FFA0B1DA8FA2D" author="Atkins, S." box="[778,919,1490,1517]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" pagination="161 - 272" refId="ref33024" refString="Atkins, S. (2005) The genus Stachytarpheta (Verbenaceae) in Brazil. Kew Bulletin 60: 161 - 272." type="journal article" year="2005">Atkins 2005</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFEEFFCFA6E4FA0B1AE8FA2C" author="Cardoso, P. H. &amp; Salimena, F. R. G." box="[929,1239,1490,1516]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" refId="ref33512" refString="Cardoso, P. H. &amp; Salimena, F. R. G. (2020 c) Stachytarpheta in Flora do Brasil 2020 under construction. Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro. Available from: http: // floradobrasil. jbrj. gov. br / reflora / floradobrasil / FB 15189 (accessed 4 January 2021)" type="url" year="2020">Cardoso &amp; Salimena 2020c</bibRefCitation>
). In 
<collectingRegion id="4994F841FFEEFFCFA043FA0B1B98FA2C" box="[1286,1447,1490,1516]" country="Brazil" name="Espirito Santo" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Espírito Santo</collectingRegion>
, it occurs in the municipalities of Conceição da Barra, Guarapari, and Vila Velha. This species is found in one SPA of this state: Reserva Estadual de Jacarenema.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEF36A3FFEEFFCFA5F8F9E71F3BF9BC" blockId="30.[136,1452,1238,2093]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFEEFFCFA5F8F9E71F60F998" bold="true" box="[189,351,1598,1624]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Phenology:—</emphasis>
Collected with flowers in January, May, August, November, and with fruits in August and November.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEF36A3FFEEFFCFA5F8F95F1F76F895" blockId="30.[136,1452,1238,2093]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFEEFFCFA5F8F95F1CAFF960" bold="true" box="[189,656,1670,1696]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Preliminary conservation assessment:</emphasis>
—This species is restricted to the 
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFEEFFCFA17EF95E1A9EF960" box="[1083,1185,1671,1696]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">restingas</emphasis>
, and has an EOO of approximately 
<quantity id="4CA89B46FFEEFFCFA471F9731F8FF904" box="[308,432,1706,1733]" metricMagnitude="7" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.25" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" unit="km" value="62500.0">62,500 km</quantity>
<superScript id="7C259BEBFFEEFFCFA4F5F9731F87F978" attach="left" box="[432,440,1706,1720]" fontSize="6" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">2</superScript>
and AOO of 
<quantity id="4CA89B46FFEEFFCFA71AF9731C95F904" box="[607,682,1706,1732]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.4" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" unit="km" value="64.0">64 km</quantity>
<superScript id="7C259BEBFFEEFFCFA7EFF9731C8DF978" attach="left" box="[682,690,1706,1720]" fontSize="6" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">2</superScript>
. It is threatened due to the loss of habitat quality because of the degradation of the 
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFEEFFCFA41FF9161FFFF928" box="[346,448,1743,1768]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">restingas</emphasis>
resulting from anthropogenic activities (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFEEFFCFA6C3F9171A26F928" author="Pereira, J. O." box="[902,1049,1742,1768]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" pagination="27 - 32" refId="ref37377" refString="Pereira, J. O. (2007) Formacoes pioneiras: restingas. In: Simonelli, M. &amp; Fraga, C. N. (Eds.) Especies da flora ameacadas de extincao no estado do Espirito Santo. IPEMA, Vitoria, pp 27 - 32." type="book chapter" year="2007">Pereira 2007</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFEEFFCFA166F9171B39F928" author="Thomazi, R. D. &amp; Rocha, R. T. &amp; Oliveira, M. V. &amp; Bruno, A. S. &amp; Silva, A. G." box="[1059,1286,1742,1768]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" pagination="1 - 6" refId="ref39633" refString="Thomazi, R. D., Rocha, R. T., Oliveira, M. V., Bruno, A. S. &amp; Silva, A. G. (2013) Um panorama da vegetacao das restingas do Espirito Santo no contexto do litoral Brasileiro. Natureza On line 11: 1 - 6." type="journal article" year="2013">
Thomazi 
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFEEFFCFA1CBF9161AF9F928" box="[1166,1222,1742,1768]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">et al.</emphasis>
2013
</bibRefCitation>
) and restricted AOO. According to 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFEEFFCFA42CF92B1C3EF8CC" author="IUCN Standards &amp; Petitions Committee" box="[361,513,1778,1804]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" refId="ref34955" refString="IUCN Standards and Petitions Committee (2019) Guidelines for Using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria. Version 14. Available from: http: // www. iucnredlist. org / documents / RedListGuidelines. pdf (accessed 30 December 2019)" type="book" year="2019">IUCN (2019)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFEEFFCFA74EF92A1C8FF8CC" authorityName="Link" authorityYear="1821" box="[523,688,1778,1805]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Stachytarpheta" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hirsutissima">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFEEFFCFA74EF92A1C8FF8CC" box="[523,688,1778,1805]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">S. hirsutissima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be considered “Endangered” (EN). However, it occurs inside PAs in 
<collectingCountry id="F3477633FFEEFFCFA59FF8CF1F21F8F0" box="[218,286,1814,1840]" name="Brazil" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Brazil</collectingCountry>
and, therefore, we adopted a more conservative point of view and considered the species “Vulnerable” VU B2ab(i,ii,iii).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEF36A3FFEEFFCFA5F8F8871B2AF800" blockId="30.[136,1452,1238,2093]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
