<paragraph id="8BEF36A3FFEEFFCEA5F8F8131C1DFEC0" blockId="30.[136,1452,1238,2093]" lastBlockId="31.[136,1451,158,293]" lastPageId="31" lastPageNumber="32" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFEEFFCFA5F8F8131F19F824" bold="true" box="[189,294,1994,2020]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Notes:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFEEFFCFA463F8131C61F824" authorityName="Link" authorityYear="1821" box="[294,606,1994,2020]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Stachytarpheta" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hirsutissima">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFEEFFCFA463F8131C61F824" box="[294,606,1994,2020]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Stachytarpheta hirsutissima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized by the presence of ovate to rotund leaves, truncate to obtuse base (some specimens that do not occur in the state of Espírito Santo have an attenuated base), and entire plant with indument hirsute. Several specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFEEFFCFA704F7CA1CDAF7EC" authorityName="Link" authorityYear="1821" box="[577,741,2066,2093]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Stachytarpheta" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hirsutissima">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFEEFFCFA704F7CA1CDAF7EC" box="[577,741,2066,2093]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">S. hirsutissima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were misidentified as 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFEEFFCFA699F7CA1B01F7EC" authority="Kunth (1818: 281)" authorityName="Kunth" authorityPageNumber="281" authorityYear="1818" box="[988,1342,2066,2093]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Lantana" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="canescens">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFEEFFCFA699F7CA1A56F7EC" box="[988,1129,2067,2093]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">S. canescens</emphasis>
Kunth (1818: 281)
</taxonomicName>
, a species from 
<collectingCountry id="F3477633FFEFFFCEA581FF471F29FF78" box="[196,278,158,184]" name="Bolivia" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="F3477633FFEFFFCEA40FFF461F42FF79" box="[330,381,159,185]" name="Peru" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Peru</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFEFFFCEA4CEFF471C25FF79" author="Atkins, S." box="[395,538,158,185]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" pagination="161 - 272" refId="ref33024" refString="Atkins, S. (2005) The genus Stachytarpheta (Verbenaceae) in Brazil. Kew Bulletin 60: 161 - 272." type="journal article" year="2005">Atkins 2005</bibRefCitation>
). These taxa are similar to each other due to the densely hirsute indument, however 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFEFFFCEA5CDFF1A1F29FF1C" authorityName="Kunth" authorityYear="1818" box="[136,278,195,221]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Lantana" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="canescens">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFEFFFCEA5CDFF1A1F29FF1C" box="[136,278,195,221]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">S. canescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has calyx more profoundly immersed in the depressions of the rachis, adaxial sinus absent and the leaves are oval-elliptical with cuneate base.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEF36A3FFEFFFCEA5F8FED31C36FEE5" blockId="31.[136,1451,158,293]" box="[189,521,266,293]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
Illustrations in 
